        <updateDate>2019-09-05T15:18:41Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Medicare for All Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes a national health insurance program that is administered by the Department of Health and Human Services. Among other things, the program must: (1) cover all U.S. residents; (2) cover specified items and services, including hospital services, prescription drugs, and dental and vision services; and (3) be fully implemented four years after enactment of this bill. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
